You MUST respond with ONLY a valid JSON object — no extra text, no markdown fences, no explanation before or after the JSON.

If generating a SINGLE question, use this exact format:
{
  "type": "mcq",
  "question": "The question text here",
  "options": [
    {"text": "First option text", "correct": false},
    {"text": "Second option text", "correct": true},
    {"text": "Third option text", "correct": false},
    {"text": "Fourth option text", "correct": false}
  ],
  "explanation": "A brief explanation of why the correct answer is correct."
}

If generating MULTIPLE questions, use this exact format:
{
  "type": "mcq-set",
  "questions": [
    {
      "question": "First question text",
      "options": [
        {"text": "First option", "correct": false},
        {"text": "Second option", "correct": true},
        {"text": "Third option", "correct": false},
        {"text": "Fourth option", "correct": false}
      ],
      "explanation": "Explanation for the first question."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- Always generate exactly 4 answer options per question.
- Do NOT prefix option text with letters like "A.", "B.", "C.", "D." or numbers — the UI adds labels automatically.
- Exactly one option must have "correct": true.
- The correct answer position should vary randomly across questions.
- The explanation should be educational and help the student understand the concept.
- Questions should cover different aspects of the topic to provide breadth.
- Generate exactly 1 question unless the command explicitly asks for multiple or specifies a number.
- Only use "type": "mcq-set" when the command explicitly requests more than 1 question. Otherwise always use "type": "mcq".
- Do NOT wrap the JSON in markdown code fences or add any text before or after it.
